metadata.name: KAKOFONI ORQUESTRA #87
metadata.description:
Check the fxhash article to read about the creative process behind it.

Click on the screen to start the music.

Keyboard commands:
1 - turn on/off the track 1
2 - turn on/off the track 1 reverb
3 - turn on/off the track 2
4 - turn on/off the track 2 reverb

I strongly recommend reloading the piece after 15 minutes (or a full play of the song), as the effects are time-related and can get lost after a long time.
The implemented features refer to the values of Hydra's brightness, contrast and modulation functions, with the lowest value being the rarest.
The way the song is performed changes every time you click on the screen.

Designed for Desktop/Notebook computers on Google Chrome Version 104.0.5112.102 (64 bits)

metadata.name: Cube Forest #71
metadata.description:
"Cube Forest" is the result of an algorithm that we have been working on for a long time. The first implementation of it was in the work entitled "Crystal Forest", below we leave the link in case you like to review it:
https://www.fxhash.xyz/generative/27686

Over time this was improved, the current work has a depth detection system for the elements of the canvas. What results in obtaining a more natural image. It also has a unique filling algorithm, capable of coloring highly complex and personalized figures. In the same way, it allows you to recreate patterns within them. Recursive forms are used to reproduce the elements of nature such as trees and grass.

metadata.name: Unstable Space #25
metadata.description:
The piece interprets the imaginary senses of an unstable space, where various disruptions might happen within its existence.

Inspired by the human tendency to need a private safe space but instead always faces a contradiction with reality. All are accumulated and abstracted into moving visual representations.
______________________________________________________________

///INTERACTIVITY///
Read the instructions below and do it after opening the live mode.

1. Press the "c" button on your computer keyboard to save a frame from your minted iteration.

2. To save a 3-second & 30 fps .GIF file, press the "s" button on your computer keyboard. Please be patient while waiting for the piece to save and render its frames.

3. The animated visual will always behave following the screen's resolution (e.g. the visual on 1:1 view and the live mode will show differently, but still give the same impression of the minted iteration). To adjust the piece resolution, you need to set your browser first and then reload the browser every time you want to capture the screen or save the rendered .GIFs file.
______________________________________________________________

Created using Hydra and p5.js

Rangga Purnama Aji, 2023
https://linktr.ee/ranggapuraji

metadata.name: Artifice #255
metadata.description:
This series is is about playful obfuscation.

The fxtext article linked on the main profect goes more in-depth into what is meant by that, as well as the events that led to this collection.

5640 bytes of Vanilla JS with no libraries. Palettes make up a third of the code.

In live mode:
‘S’ : save as png (3000 × 3600)
’V’ : save as svg (without grain)

URL params in live mode:
‘g=n’ : no grain
‘g=p’ : paper grain
‘h=t’ : high resolution mode, 9000 ×10600 (Chrome only, and may take a moment)

For example, if you wanted paper grain in high resolution, append “&g=p&h=t” to the url in live mode.

After rendering with these params, tapping 'P' will then save a png with those settings applied.
